#! <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
#! <TRANSFORMER
# TRANSFORMER_BEGIN ATTRIBUTE_MAPPER_AND_LENGTH_CHECKER,1,"""FGP Tools""",ecd771f7-1cc5-4650-92ec-3854d20a1861,"Linked by Default",No,NO_PARALLELISM,,No,25241,YES,No,313,No,
# <p><strong>Description </strong></p>
# <p>This custom transformer edits (maps) values specified in an input file to a specified attribute. It also checks the number of characters of this attribute to a specified value. It output through the TO_LONG port the features for wich the attribute is to long and and not mapped. The specified attribute can be a list or not. It uses the METADATA_VALUE_MAPPER_NG custom transformer for which the description is below.</p>
# <p><strong>Input Ports </strong></p>
# <ul>
# <li>DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.</li>
# </ul>
# <p><strong>Output Ports </strong></p>
# <ul>
# <li>
# <p>CORRECT_LENGTH: The processed output metadata records with value mapped and attribute length verified.</p>
# </li>
# <li>
# <p>TOO_LONG: The processed output metdata records value mapped and for wich the attribute length is to long.</p>
# </li>
# </ul>
# <p><strong>Parameters </strong></p>
# <ul>
# <li>
# <p>IN_ATT_TO_MAP: Name of the attribute on wich the mapping and the length verification needs to be done. It can be a list attribute or not.</p>
# </li>
# <li>
# <p>IN_CHAR_LIMIT: Number of characters over wich the attribute will be compare (smaller or equal to).</p>
# </li>
# <li>
# <p>METADATA_VALUE_MAPPER_NG params: See next section</p>
# </li>
# </ul>
# <hr />
# <p><p style="text-align: center;">METADATA_VALUE_MAPPER_NG </p></p>
# <p>This custom transformer edits (maps) values to valid English values (if requested) and valid French values equivalent (if requested) and value code RI_CODES (if requested).  The name of the attribute to map and French, English and RI_CODES action are parametrizable.  </p>
# <p>Note: If the attribute ou attribute list is not present on the feature an error is created.  If the element to map is not present in the lookup table an error is created.</p>
# <p><strong>Input Ports </strong></p>
# <ul>
# <li>DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.</li>
# </ul>
# <p><strong>Output Ports </strong></p>
# <ul>
# <li>OUTPUT: The process output metdata records with value mapped.</li>
# </ul>
# <p><strong>Parameters </strong></p>
# <ul>
# <li>
# <p>ATT_TO_MAP: Name of the FME attribute or FME list attribute to map in plain text (ex.: 'format' or 'resources{}.format').  Do not use the Open Text Editor &gt; FME Feature Attribute option to select the attribute to map;</p>
# </li>
# <li>
# <p>ERROR_NOT_MAPPED: Flag use to map data values that cannot be found in the loopup tables. Can take 2 values: Yes: map data values not found; No: Do not map data values not found;</p>
# </li>
# <li>
# <p>ENGLISH_REFRESH: Flag use for updating English attribute value. Can take two value: Yes: update English attribute value; No do not update English attribute value;</p>
# </li>
# <li>
# <p>FRENCH_REFRESH: Flag use for creating or updating French attribute value. Can take two value: Yes: update French attribute value; No do not update French atribute value;</p>
# </li>
# <li>
# <p>CODE_REFRESH: Flag use for creating updating the RI_CODES. Can take two value: Yes: update the code; No do not update the code;</p>
# </li>
# <li>
# <p>FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);</p>
# </li>
# <li>
# <p>IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;</p>
# </li>
# <li>
# <p>P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.</p>
# </li>
# </ul>
# TRANSFORMER_END
#!   A0_PREVIEW_IMAGE="data:image/png;base64,"
#!   ARCGIS_COMPATIBILITY="ARCGIS_AUTO"
#!   ATTR_TYPE_ENCODING="SDF"
#!   BLOCKED_LOOPING="No"
#!   CATEGORY="&quot;FGP Tools&quot;"
#!   DESCRIPTION="&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;This custom transformer edits (maps) values specified in an input file to a specified attribute. It also checks the number of characters of this attribute to a specified value. It output through the TO_LONG port the features for wich the attribute is to long and and not mapped. The specified attribute can be a list or not. It uses the METADATA_VALUE_MAPPER_NG custom transformer for which the description is below.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;CORRECT_LENGTH: The processed output metadata records with value mapped and attribute length verified.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;TOO_LONG: The processed output metdata records value mapped and for wich the attribute length is to long.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;IN_ATT_TO_MAP: Name of the attribute on wich the mapping and the length verification needs to be done. It can be a list attribute or not.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;IN_CHAR_LIMIT: Number of characters over wich the attribute will be compare (smaller or equal to).&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;METADATA_VALUE_MAPPER_NG params: See next section&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;hr /&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;METADATA_VALUE_MAPPER_NG &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;This custom transformer edits (maps) values to valid English values (if requested) and valid French values equivalent (if requested) and value code RI_CODES (if requested).  The name of the attribute to map and French, English and RI_CODES action are parametrizable.  &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;Note: If the attribute ou attribute list is not present on the feature an error is created.  If the element to map is not present in the lookup table an error is created.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;OUTPUT: The process output metdata records with value mapped.&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;ATT_TO_MAP: Name of the FME attribute or FME list attribute to map in plain text (ex.: &apos;format&apos; or &apos;resources{}.format&apos;).  Do not use the Open Text Editor &amp;gt; FME Feature Attribute option to select the attribute to map;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;ERROR_NOT_MAPPED: Flag use to map data values that cannot be found in the loopup tables. Can take 2 values: Yes: map data values not found; No: Do not map data values not found;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;ENGLISH_REFRESH: Flag use for updating English attribute value. Can take two value: Yes: update English attribute value; No do not update English attribute value;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;FRENCH_REFRESH: Flag use for creating or updating French attribute value. Can take two value: Yes: update French attribute value; No do not update French atribute value;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;CODE_REFRESH: Flag use for creating updating the RI_CODES. Can take two value: Yes: update the code; No do not update the code;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;"
