ist attribute to map in plain text (ex.: &apos;format&apos; or &apos;resources{}.format&apos;).  Do not use the Open Text Editor &gt; FME Feature Attribute option to select the attribute to map;&#10;&#10; - ERROR_NOT_MAPPED: Flag use to map data values that cannot be found in the loopup tables. Can take 2 values: Yes: map data values not found; No: Do not map data values not found;&#10;&#10; - ENGLISH_REFRESH: Flag use for updating English attribute value. Can take two value: Yes: update English attribute value; No do not update English attribute value;&#10;&#10; - FRENCH_REFRESH: Flag use for creating or updating French attribute value. Can take two value: Yes: update French attribute value; No do not update French atribute value;&#10;&#10; - CODE_REFRESH: Flag use for creating updating the RI_CODES. Can take two value: Yes: update the code; No do not update the code;&#10;&#10; - FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);&#10;&#10; - IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;&#10; &#10; - P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.&#10;"
